(255,	1,	'2015-01-03 13:03:32',	'2015-01-03 13:03:32',	'\n				I have so many things to thank for last year. I was able to meet new people, learn new things and travel different places.\n\nHighlights:\n\n<strong>March 2014 - Went to Japan (Tokyo then to Osaka), then got engaged to the love of my life</strong>\n\nGoing to Japan was my dream since a child. On March 2014, my dream came true. I arrived at Narita Airport and fetched by my girlfriend. I stayed in her place in Shonandai. I also proposed to her and she said yes!\n\nI also experienced the transition from snow to the cherry blossom season. My travel was on the right timing.\n\nI also rode the shinkansen and met Ashley\'s family in Befu.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_256\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_0865.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-256\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_0865.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Near Lake Tanuki\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Near Lake Tanuki[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_257\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_0901.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-257\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_0901.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Snow remnants \" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Snow remnants[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_258\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1030.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-258\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1030.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Just happy together\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Just happy together[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_259\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1341.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-259\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1341.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Waiting for the Shinkansen to Osaka\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Waiting for the Shinkansen to Osaka[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_260\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1653.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-260\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1653.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"With Ashley\'s dad and brother\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> With Ashley\'s dad and brother[/caption]\n\n<strong>April 2014 - My paper was published in Asia Pacific Chronicle</strong>\n\nThank you APC for supporting!\n\n<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/1964909_763613600324137_1191120663_n.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-262 aligncenter\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/1964909_763613600324137_1191120663_n.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"1964909_763613600324137_1191120663_n\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<strong>April 2014 - Baler Trip with APC colleagues and friends</strong>\n\nI was invited to join my very good and nice Atenean colleagues (haha, majority of them) from APC. They are actually from the School of Accountancy and Business (SOAB) but we became friends when my work cubicle was placed near them. We stayed in Bay\'s Inn. The food and beach were very awesome. We went to the Mother Falls, visited the Baler Museum, heard mass in their church and visited a very old tree in Aurora.\n\nI also attempted to do surfing. But I really need to lose weight before attempting another one. hehehe\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_268\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1735.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-268\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1735.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Dawn at Baler, Aurora\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Dawn at Baler, Aurora[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_267\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1720.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-267\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1720.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Breakfast time!!\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Breakfast time!![/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_266\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1884.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-266\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1884.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"With that spooky old tree\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> With that spooky old tree[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_265\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1864.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-265\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1864.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Beside the bust of Manuel Quezon\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Beside the bust of Manuel Quezon[/caption]\n\n<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_1826.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-264 aligncenter\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_1826.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"IMG_1826\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n<strong>April 2014- Pagsanjan Trip with the family</strong>\n\nWe went to Pagsanjan for the Holy Week. We rode a small boat to go to Pagsanjan falls. There were so many Korean tourists there! Pagsanjan has a good LTE signal but the lodging places there are not so good.\n\nWe stayed in Lagos del Sol (the place was very peaceful and elegant). I recommend it for those who would like a serene and clean place.\n\nWe did some polo barong shopping in Lumban and slippers/shoe shopping in Liliw. We stopped in Los Banos to buy the original buko pie and cow\'s milk and chocolate drink. The traffic in Los Banos to Calamba, however, was stand still. (more family bonding time!)\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_270\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2039.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-270 size-medium\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2039.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"IMG_2039\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Getting ready for some boating[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_271\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2037.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-271\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2037.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"With Joseph and Nicole\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> With Joseph and Nicole[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_272\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2021.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-272\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2021.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"It\'s the lake!\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> It\'s the lake![/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_273\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2024.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-273\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2024.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Lagos del Sol grounds\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Lagos del Sol grounds[/caption]\n\n<strong> May 2014- General Santos Trip with the family</strong>\n\nIt was my first time to go to Mindanao and I find it peaceful and progressive. I think the media is responsible for giving us a very negative impression of Mindanao.\n\nWe went to the famous KCC Mall of Gensan. We alo went to SM and Robinsons. The Pacman Gym is just across SM Gensan.\n\nWe went for a 2-hour drive to White Haven Beach Resort in Glan. We were at the bottom of the Philippines! The beach was very natural and the place was far from the city. It\'s not commercialized. It\'s a virgin place and a quiet one.\n\n<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2256.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-275 aligncenter\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2256.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"IMG_2256\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_276\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2182.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-276\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2182.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Gen Santos Airport\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Gen Santos Airport[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_277\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2184.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-277\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2184.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"It\'s Jinkee\'s store!\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> It\'s Jinkee\'s store at KCC Mall of Gensan[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_278\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2185.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-278\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2185.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Happy 14th Birthday Joey Boy!\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Happy 14th Birthday Joey Boy![/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_279\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2198.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-279\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2198.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Tricycle ride to the beach\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Tricycle ride to the beach[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_280\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2208.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-280\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2208.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Beach at White Haven, Glan\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Beach at White Haven, Glan[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_281\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2210.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2210.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Beach at White Haven, Glan (That\'s the Celebes Sea. Can you see Malaysia/Indonesia?)\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Beach at White Haven, Glan<br />(That\'s the Celebes Sea. Can you see Malaysia/Indonesia?)[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_282\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2240.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-282\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2240.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Citra Mina, where you buy seafood that you can take home. They have good packaging.\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Citra Mina, where you buy seafood that you can take home. They have good packaging.[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_283\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2255.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-283\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2255.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Blugre Coffee in Robinsons Gen San\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Blugre Coffee in Robinsons Gen San[/caption]\n\n<strong>May 2014 - Pico de Loro Trip with the family c/o Coca-Cola</strong>\n\nWe went to the annual company Family Day at Coca-Cola in Pico de Loro. It was a long drive from Makati to Batangas. The place looks very elegant but the beach is not good compared to the one in Glan. haha The White Haven beach resort set the standards. :)\n\nThere was plenty of food prepared by the company. We did some kayaking and used the swimming pool. There were plenty of Coke giveaways in the end. It was a tiresome day for us.\n\n<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2296.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-285 aligncenter\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2296.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"IMG_2296\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_286\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2299.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-286\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2299.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"w/ Joseph Dan\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> w/ Joseph Dan[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_287\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2300.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-287\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2300.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Coca-Cola, Share the Happiness\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Coca-Cola, Share the Happiness[/caption]\n\n<strong>August 2014 - Attended Joan\'s Wedding in Subic with friends</strong>\n\nCongrats to Joan Diaz-Ruiz, a college friend of mine who got married to Jordan Ruiz. It was also a reunion with the Plaridel friends after a long time not seeing each other.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_290\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2726.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-290\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2726.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"w/ Art and Lance\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> w/ Art and Lance[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_289\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/10410132_10152573930663446_6049258477485148390_n.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-289\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/10410132_10152573930663446_6049258477485148390_n.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"w/ the bride, Joan Diaz-Ruiz\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a> w/ the bride, Joan Diaz-Ruiz[/caption]\n\n<strong>August 2014 - Move-in at current home in Quezon City</strong>\n\nAfter 3 years of saving money, I have finally moved in my current home here in Quezon City. The renovation was very costly. At this point, there\'s no money left in my wallet haha\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_297\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/10672061_844209925597837_4130628599579472571_n.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-297\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/10672061_844209925597837_4130628599579472571_n.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"View from the terrace\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> View from the terrace[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_295\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2610.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-295\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2610.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Shower area and toilet\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Shower area and toilet[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_293\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2608.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-293\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2608.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Under construction, entrance and kitchen\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Under construction, entrance and kitchen[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_292\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2607.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-292\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2607.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"So many expenses! Need to write everything down. hahaha\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> So many expenses! Need to write everything down. hahaha[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_299\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_26091.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-299\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_26091.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Stairs and baluster\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Stairs and baluster[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_298\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2554.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-298\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2554.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Terrace under construction\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Terrace under construction[/caption]\n\n<strong>August 2014 - Birthday celebration with the Lolas in Cavite and family</strong>\n\nActually, I do not anymore want to have a big celebration in my birthday. But my grandmas always want to have a celebration. So I stayed in Cavite and spent time with them on my birthday which fell on a weekday.\n\nI went for an afternoon mass in St. Alphonsus, Magallanes. Then we went for a KTV night with the family.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_304\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_29081.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-304\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_29081.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"From Japan with love. Thanks baby!\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> From Japan with love. Thanks baby![/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_301\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2924.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-301\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2924.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Videoke night (Mama\'s idea! Enjoyed very much)\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Videoke night (Mama\'s idea! Enjoyed very much)[/caption]\n\n<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2920.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-303 aligncenter\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2920.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"IMG_2920\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n<strong>September 2014 - Ashley\'s sponsored trip to Manila</strong>\n\nIt was a late birthday gift but it was planned. Ashley\'s visiting Manila for an event called \"Kawaii in Manila.\" The event was a success. I met her new friends, Kaila, Anne Kate, Kaye, Erick and Tricia.\n\nShe was able to meet my colleagues in Coca-Cola. We had a post-birthday celebration in Elias, The Fort BGC.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_306\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2993.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-306\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2993.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"That\'s my girl! So cheerful and lively.\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> That\'s my girl! So cheerful and lively.[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_307\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2999.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-307\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2999.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"w/ Tricia Gosingtian\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> w/ Tricia Gosingtian[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_308\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_3019.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-308\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_3019.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Ashley Dy modelling Harajuku fashion\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Ashley Dy modelling Harajuku fashion[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_309\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_3025.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-309\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_3025.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"w/ our friend Art\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> w/ our friend Art[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_310\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_3031.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-310\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_3031.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"w/ Kaila Ocampo, one of the founders of Kawaii in Manila\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> w/ Kaila Ocampo, one of the founders of Kawaii in Manila[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_312\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_2990.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-312\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_2990.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"My students from APC \" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> My students from APC[/caption]\n\n<strong>October 2014 - Housewarming with friends and family\n</strong>\n\nThere were 2 batches of housewarming. I don\'t have pictures of the second batch with my Coca-Cola officemates. But I have to acknowledge Sheryll for bringing in some food. Thank you!!\n\nThe visitors in the first housewarming were my college friends plus Lance (boyfriend of Kenwin) and Jordan (husband of Joan). We had a simple pot luck and played the board game \"Resistance.\" It was a very fun game!\n\nSpecial mention to the following donors haha:\n\nJonna - for the Ikea alarm clock\n\nNinong Erick - for the wall clock\n\nMy dad - for the induction cooker and expensive pan haha\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_315\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"https://justinpineda.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/img_3260.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-315\" src=\"https://justinspeaks.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/img_3260.jpg?w=225\" alt=\"Thanks Papa for the induction cooker and the expensive pan. haha\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Thanks Papa for the induction cooker and the expensive pan. haha[/caption]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_316\" align=\"alignc